Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced). Mince @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(minced). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and halve @lemon{1}(zested and halved). Mince @jalapeño{1}(minced, ribs and seeds removed for less heat). Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(halved lengthwise, cut into ½-inch-thick half-moons). Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%400g can}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add ¼ of the onion; cook, stirring, until just softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @water{1%cup}, half the @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}; bring to a boil. Add @quinoa{1/2%cup}; cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until quinoa is tender and water has absorbed, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Chermoula ==

While quinoa cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine cilantro, @olive oil{2%tbsp}, a pinch of garlic, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. Add lemon juice to taste and as much jalapeño as you like. Taste and add more garlic if desired.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{3%tbsp}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and as much lemon zest as you like. Add @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Tagine ==

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and remaining onion. Cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add @Tunisian spice blend{1%tbsp}, remaining garlic, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @water{1/3%cup} and remaining @veggie stock concentrate{1} to pan with veggies.

Stir in chickpeas and bring tagine to a low simmer. Cook until liquid has slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

== To Serve ==

Fluff quinoa with a fork; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Divide quinoa between plates and top with tagine, @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce}, and @dried apricots{1%ounce}. Drizzle with lemon crema and chermoula. Drizzle with @?hot sauce{1%tsp} if desired. Cut any remaining lemon into wedges and serve on the side.

> Toast almonds before adding if you like for extra crunch.